  <title>get_position</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gdouble, Clutter.Knot)
@returns(guint)
def get_position(progress, position)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The value in @progress represents a position along the path where
0.0 is the beginning and 1.0 is the end of the path. An
interpolated position is then stored in @position.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>progress :</p></td>
<td><p>a position along the path as a fraction of its length</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>position :</p></td>
<td><p>location to store the position</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>Returns :</p></td>
<td><p>index of the node used to calculate the position.</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.0</p>
